	<h1>COMPUTING SCIENCE GRADUATE STUDENTS' ASSOCIATION CONSTITUTION</h1>
<ol>
<li>Name and Purpose</li>
<ol>
<li>The name shall be the Computing Science Graduate Students' Association.</li>
<li>The purpose of the Association is to promote the welfare of the Computing Science graduate students, and to provide official representation for them.</li>
</ol>
<li>Membership</li>
<ol>
<li>All graduate and qualifying students registered in the School of Computing Science at Simon Fraser University shall be members of the Association.</li>
</ol>
<li>Executive</li>
<ol>
<li>The Executive of the Association shall consist of a president, a vice-president, a secretary, and a treasurer.</li>
<li>The Executive shall act for the members in matters concerning the routine business of the Association.</li>
<li>The President shall co-ordinate all business of the Association.</li>
<li>In the absence of the President, the Vice-President shall act in his or her place.</li>
<li>The Treasurer (Vice-President Finance) shall handle the correspondence, record keeping, and finances of the Association.</li>
<li>The Secretary (Vice-President Administration) takes minutes at the meetings of the Association, and distributes it to the other members.</li>
<li>The Vice-President Communications maintains the webpages and the CS grad students photo board</li>
<li>The Vice-President Social Affairs organizes social gatherings of the Association</li>
<li>Further duties of the Executive shall be specified in the By-laws.</li>
</ol>
<li>Officers of the Association</li>
<ol>
<li>Officers of the Association shall consist of the Executive plus members elected to positions or committees designated in the By-laws.</li>
</ol>
<li>Meetings</li>
<ol>
<li>Meetings of the Association shall be held at least once per semester.</li>
<li>The Executive must honour a petition requesting a meeting, if it is signed by at least ten percent of the membership, by calling a meeting of the Association within one week of receipt of the petition.</li>
<li>A quorum at any meeting of the Association shall consist of ten persons of the current membership not on leave.</li>
<li>A meeting shall not be called to order unless a quorum is present.</li>
<li>The Chair at a meeting of the Association shall not vote except when a deciding vote is necessary.</li>
<li>With approval of the Executive, non-members of the Association may attend but not vote at meetings of the Association.</li>
</ol>
<li>Amendments</li>
<ol>
<li>The constitution shall be amended by a two-thirds majority vote at a meeting of the Association and shall require a notice of motion to be sent to all members at least one week prior to the meeting.</li>
<li>By-Laws shall be amended by a two-thirds majority vote at any meeting of the Association.</li>
</ol>
<li>Petition</li>
<ol>
<li>Any petition signed by ten percent of the membership and submitted to all members of the Association shall be discussed and voted upon at the next meeting of the Association.</li>
</ol>
<li>Elections and Terms of Office</li>
<ol>
<li>The Officers of the Association shall normally be chosen each semester from the members of the Association, by majority votes at a meeting or at meetings of the Association to be held at a time or at times specified within the By-Laws.</li>
<li>Officers of the Association shall normally hold office until their successors are duly elected.</li>
<li>Officers of the Association may be re-elected to the same or any other office provided their membership is valid.</li>
<li>Members of the Association may remove an Officer of the Association from office by a majority vote at a meeting of the Association if a notice of motion has been sent to all members at least one week prior to the meeting.</li>
<li>Officers of the Association may resign from office by tendering their resignation to the Executive.</li>
<li>The Executive may appoint a member, with his or her consent, to fill any vacant office.</li>
<li>Any member who withdraws from the Computing Science graduate studies program shall be considered to have resigned their position.</li>
</ol>
<li>Ad Hoc Committees</li>
<ol>
<li>Ad Hoc Committees shall be formed or dissolved by a majority vote at any meeting of the Association.</li>
<li>Terms of Reference for an Ad Hoc Committee shall be specified at the time of the Committee's formation.</li>
<li>Membership of an Ad Hoc Committee shall be established by the Association at the time of formation of the Committee.</li>
<li>The members of an Ad Hoc Committee shall be elected when the Committee is formed.</li>
<li>A Chair of an Ad Hoc Committee may be elected by the members of that Committee.</li>
<li>The Chair of an Ad Hoc Committee shall not vote at a meeting of that Committee unless a deciding vote is necessary.</li>
<li>The Chair of an Ad Hoc Committee shall have the right to represent that Committee at meetings by speaking and voting on matters within that Committee's Terms of Reference.</li>
</ol></ol> <div class="attachmentsContainer">

